      "id": "8d3a16d6c87592ab51ee3d929a8ce4743e49e6c1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 126,
        "name": "Ned Bass",
        "email": "bass6@llnl.gov",
        "username": "nedbass"
      },
      "date": "2014-08-27 21:28:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nWe can't have these functions follow a completely different convention for returning errors than the rest of the llapi_layout API.  If we want to change the convention then we need a separate patch to change it across the board. I personally consider the old llapi convention of returning negative errno contrary to common practice for user space libraries, and I intentionally broke from it in the new API.  But either way, we need to be consistent within the llapi_layout_ namespace.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
